(November 13, 1957)

(Republished)

Michael Barron et al., Copartners Doing Business as M. Barron, et al., Respondents, v. Farm Bureau Mutual Automobile Insurance Company, and Its Successor in Interest Nationwide Mutual Insurance Company, Appellant.

Order unanimously affirmed, with $20 costs and disbursements to the respondents. No opinion. Concur—Peck, P. J., Breitel, Botein, Rabin and Valente, JJ. [See ante, p. 941.]
